Poland's PGNiG Plans to Bid for Vattenfall’s Polish Assets, SPEC in 2011

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-03-24T05:59:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/poland-s-pgnig-plans-to-bid-for-vattenfall-s-polish-assets-spec-in-2011.html
Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i
Gazownictwo SA (PGN) , Poland’s dominant gas company, plans to bid for
Vattenfall AB’s Warsaw heat and power assets this year, the
company known as PGNiG said in a regulatory statement on March
22. PGNiG values the purchase at 2.8 billion zloty ($978
million) to 3.2 billion zloty.  The company also plans to buy SPEC SA, Warsaw’s heating
network operator, that the capital is selling this year. PGNiG
values SPEC at 740 million zloty to 1 billion zloty.  Gornictwo is also interested in a 300 million-zloty to 400
million-zloty purchase of hydropower plant ZEW Nidzica SA that
the Polish government plans to offer for sale this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maciej Martewicz at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net  